(City Press) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Nairobi - A presidential election due in Burundi next month should be postponed indefinitely until political stability returns, President Jacob Zuma said on Tuesday, summarising the outcome of a regional summit in Angola.The special meeting was convened after a failed coup in Burundi against President Pierre Nkurunziza, whose decision to seek a third term of office has triggered weeks of street protests. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.